# Code Ownership Rules
# https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/managing-your-repositorys-settings-and-features/customizing-your-repository/about-code-owners

# Default owner for everything
* @technical-lead

# Shared packages require extra scrutiny
# Changes to shared packages affect all client sites
/packages/ @technical-lead @senior-developer

# UI components - require design and accessibility review
/packages/ui-components/ @technical-lead @frontend-lead

# SEO utilities - require SEO specialist review
/packages/seo-utils/ @technical-lead @seo-specialist

# CMS configuration - require content strategy review
/packages/cms-config/ @technical-lead @content-strategist

# Documentation - all contributors can review
/docs/ @technical-lead @senior-developer

# CI/CD workflows - require DevOps review
/.github/workflows/ @technical-lead @devops-lead

# Project constitution and core architecture
/CLAUDE.md @technical-lead
/task_deps.md @technical-lead

# Client sites - site-specific ownership
# Add specific owners per client site as needed
# /sites/client-a/ @client-a-lead
# /sites/client-b/ @client-b-lead
